Hongi
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a Maori. Usu. in pl. (the Hongis); prob. from Hongi Hika, name of an early Maori chief well known from school history books; poss. chiefly a Si term, as unlike Hori, it is not used by Maoris among themselves.


Origin: Maori
Register: offensive

Register 2: obsolete
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: ca1949 common use in Havelock, and on the West Coast and also as an attrib: eg. `That hongi kid.'
